---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="About | Leonard Wall" description="About Leonard Wall and his work across security, observability, and platform strategy.">
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-content px-6 py-20">
    <p class="text-sm uppercase tracking-[0.22em] text-accent">About</p>
    <h1 class="mt-3 text-4xl font-semibold tracking-tight md:text-5xl">An executive perspective on resilience, platforms, and complexity</h1>
    <div class="mt-8 grid gap-10 lg:grid-cols-[1.05fr_.95fr]">
      <div class="space-y-6 text-base leading-8 text-muted">
        <p>
          Leonard Wall is a technology executive focused on the convergence of security, observability, and modern platform strategy. His work centers on helping organizations reduce complexity, improve resilience, and create stronger alignment across engineering, operations, and cyber.
        </p>
        <p>
          His background spans enterprise security leadership, digital transformation, regulatory environments, and executive advisory work. That range allows him to bridge the strategic and operational layers of modern technology decisions.
        </p>
        <p>
          Today, his writing and projects focus on platformization, telemetry as a strategic asset, executive decision velocity, and the practical overlap between observability and security.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-3xl border border-line bg-panel p-8 shadow-soft">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text">Core themes</h2>
        <ul class="mt-5 space-y-4 text-sm leading-7 text-muted">
          <li><span class="font-semibold text-text">Security and observability convergence</span><br />A more unified model for detection, response, and operational resilience.</li>
          <li><span class="font-semibold text-text">Platform strategy</span><br />Reducing tool sprawl and improving decision quality across the enterprise.</li>
          <li><span class="font-semibold text-text">Executive communication</span><br />Translating technical complexity into strategic language leaders can act on.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
